KnownLibraries.Name: IWatchdog
KnownLibraries.Author: Venelin Efremov, Frederic Pillon
KnownLibraries.Sentence: Enables support for independent watchdog (IWDG) hardware on STM32 processors.
KnownLibraries.Paragraph: Independent watchdog (IWDG) is a hardware timer on the chip which would generate a reset condition if the time is not reloaded within the specified time. It is generally used in production systems to reset the system if the CPU becomes "stuck".

KnownLibraries.Name: Mouse
KnownLibraries.Author: Arduino
KnownLibraries.Sentence: Allows an Arduino board with USB capabilities to act as a Mouse. For Leonardo/Micro only
KnownLibraries.Paragraph: This library plugs on the HID library. Can be used with or without other HID-based libraries (Keyboard, Gamepad etc)

KnownLibraries.Name: SoftwareSerial
KnownLibraries.Author: Arduino, Armin van der Togt
KnownLibraries.Sentence: Enables serial communication on any digital pin.
KnownLibraries.Paragraph: The SoftwareSerial library has been developed to allow serial communication on any digital pin of the board, using software to replicate the functionality of the hardware UART. It is possible to have multiple software serial ports.

KnownLibraries.Name: EEPROM
KnownLibraries.Author: Arduino, Christopher Andrews
KnownLibraries.Sentence: Enables reading and writing to the permanent board storage.
KnownLibraries.Paragraph: This library allows to read and write data in a memory type, the EEPROM, that keeps its content also when the board is powered off. The amount of EEPROM available depends on the microcontroller type.

KnownLibraries.Name: CMSIS_DSP
KnownLibraries.Author: Frederic Pillon
KnownLibraries.Sentence: Add CMSIS DSP software library, a suite of common signal processing functions for use on Cortex-M processor based devices.
KnownLibraries.Paragraph: The library is divided into a number of functions each covering a specific category: Basic math functions, Fast math functions, Complex math functions, Filters, Matrix functions, Transform functions, Motor control functions, Statistical functions, Support functions, Interpolation functions. The library has separate functions for operating on 8-bit integers, 16-bit integers, 32-bit integer and 32-bit floating-point value.

KnownLibraries.Name: Servo
KnownLibraries.Author: Michael Margolis, Arduino
KnownLibraries.Sentence: Allows Arduino/Genuino boards to control a variety of servo motors.
KnownLibraries.Paragraph:
This library can control a great number of servos.
It makes careful use of timers: the library can control 12 servos using only 1 timer.
On the Arduino Due you can control up to 60 servos.
